FYI <#1268377668831809669> The election is mere weeks away, and vast amounts of pressure is now on Nebraska lawmakers to change the game‚Äôs rules before it even begins. So let‚Äôs call this exactly what it is: a brazen attempt at a power grab by special interests, outsiders, and politicians who want to get their way at all costs ‚Äì even if it means removing a powerful Nebraska legacy. 

Remember: How Nebraska awards its electoral votes sets our state apart and unites us. While most other states give all their electoral college votes to the candidate who wins the popular vote in the state, in Nebraska, we can allocate our votes by congressional district. This is a Nebraska tradition because of our deeply nonpartisan heritage that promotes fair representation and boosts participation on Election Day.

Nebraska‚Äôs split electoral vote system has worked for over 30 years, ensuring fair representation for all voters. Returning to a winner-take-all approach would ignore Nebraska‚Äôs diverse voices and political landscape. Our current system ensures that urban and rural areas are represented fairly, fosters greater voter engagement, and prevents any one party from monopolizing our state‚Äôs electoral votes. This system has given Nebraska unique influence on the national stage, and there‚Äôs no valid reason to abandon a method that empowers all voters and preserves fairness.

Regarding what Randy wrote above, this article goes into detail about how this could go: https://abcnews.go.com/Politics/republicans-step-effort-change-nebraskas-electoral-vote-process/story?id=113852074
